<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-730-520  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 730 520.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Oct 2 1989 v6 n39 p14(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>High-end repeater capable of connecting 80 Ethernet segments.andO;(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Grygo, Gene.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>BICC Data Networks' Isolan 1200 Multi-Media Modular RepeaterSystem is a modular repeater which can support up to 1,160workstations on 80 segments of an Ethernet network.andP;  The repeaterworks with unshielded twisted pair, coaxial, and fiber-optic cableand supports high-speed links to remote sites.andP;  The repeater has aredundant power supply, a rack-mountable chassis, a managementcard, up to ten repeater line cards and eight ports.andP;  A fullnetwork management option that resides entirely on the networkmanagement card is also available.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   BICC Data Networks Ltd. (product introduction).andO;Product:   BICC Data Networks Isolan 1200 Multi-Media Modular Repeater System(Computer communications equipment) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionRepeatersNetworksEthernetBridges (Connector)Twisted PairCoaxial CablesFiber OpticsNetwork Management.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>High-End Repeater Capable of Connecting 80 Ethernet SegmentsandM;WESTBOROUGH, Mass.andP;  -- BICC Data Networks has introduced a modular repeaterthat links as many as 80 Ethernet segments and supports as many as 1,160workstations, officials said.andM;The Isolan 1200 Multi-Media Modular Repeater System can support multiplecable types such as unshielded twisted pair, thick and thin Ethernet coaxial,and fiber-optic.andP;  Also, the different local area netork segments can bewithin the same building or be connected by high-speed links.andM;The repeater has a redundant power supply and repeater logic on each medialine card, officials said.andM;&quot;Unlike competitive products, which have one repeater per enclosure, each ofour media line cards has its own repeater, ensuring that a local failure onlyimpacts users on that particular card rather than all users on the entireenclosure,&quot; said Jack Simpson, a vice president of marketing for BICC.andM;The system has a rack-mountable chassis that incorporates one or twoload-sharing power supplies, a management card and as many as 10 repeaterline cards linked to a repeater and as many as eight ports, depending on themedia type.andM;A fully supported network management option is available that resides on thenetwork management card, officials said.andM;Remote Bridge, TooandM;BICC has also introduced the Isolan 1435 Remote Bridge, which connectsdispersed Ethernet LANs to digital or analog wide area networks, officialssaid.andM;The bridge supports two WAN links and speeds up to 128Kbits per second overeach link.andP;  Each WAN link can support the RS-232-C, RS-449, V.32 or X.21interfaces.andM;Prices for the 1200 Multi-Media Modular Repeater System, which the companywill begin shipping in decembeR, will start at $3,585 for unshieldedtwisted-pair wiring.andM;The 1435 Remote Bridge, available now, is priced at $6,300 with a standardV.35 interface.andP;  A secondary interface option is available for a V.35,RS-232-C, RS-449 or X.21 interface for $800.andM;BICC Data Networks Inc. can be reached at 1800 West Park Drive, Westborough,MA 01581, (508) 898-2422.andO;</TEXT></DOC>